The order of head:

package statement;
import statement;
class/interface definations.

package com.foo;
In file /root/com/foo/X.java
public class Y trys to accessing class X in another package.

classes in the same package can accessing to each other without import anything.

import com.foo.*; //package import does not use static keyword like import static com.foo.*

import static com.foo.X.*;
import static com.foo.X.Logicid;//import static package.classname.* or package.classname.fieldname.

If Y accessing through X.Logicid, then no static import required.If the code is System.print(Logicid),then static